{{Quote|Eyes half closed, tongue curled up to just touch the roof of the mouth: the Force running in a wheel from the top of one's head, spilling down through one's spine, then the marrow of one's thighbones, then draining from the pressure point in the soles of the feet to discharge.|Yoda describing silent meditation|<ref name="Yoda: Dark Rendezvous">''[[Yoda: Dark Rendezvous]]''</ref>}}
'''Silent Meditation''' was one of the many meditative techniques found in the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] at the time of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]; other forms included "[[tidal breathing]]" and the common [[seven-second relaxation technique]]. Taught to young pupils by the wise [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]], the centering exercise was used by countless [[Padawan/Legends|Padawans]] and [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Knights]], often while embroiled in dangerous situations, such as when trapped on a hostile [[Planet/Legends|planet]], shrouded in the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]].

